posts.name: Batu Altınay
posts.cooked: Our PDH gave an error even though there’s no wiring issue and other devices are working fine. How can I reach the bootloader and reset the PDH? (Attached is a video showing the PDH status light colors.)

posts.name: Carter Ryba
posts.cooked: How hidden is your CAN wire? The reason I ask is because there might be a break in your wire causing issues. Does any device appear in the REV hardware client?

posts.name: Batu Altınay
posts.cooked: When we attach PDH, there is no CAN device, but when we attach any spark, we can see every device in the bus excluding PDH.

posts.name: Batu Altınay
posts.cooked: and no we dont have any hardware problem

posts.name: Carter Ryba
posts.cooked: When you use a USB cable connected to a SparkMAX you can see everything on the CANbus but when you use a USB cable connected to the PDH REV's Power Distribution Hub you can't see anything on the CANbus.

posts.name: Ahmet Melih Şen
posts.cooked: Correction: We can't see any device except for the SPARK itself. When plugging into the PDH there's a 'CAN Bus Off' sticky fault that can't be cleared, and looking at the CAN bus shows about 5 Bus Off errors every second.

posts.name: Carter Ryba
posts.cooked: I can't really tell from the video—is the termination switch turned on or off on your REV's Power Distribution Hub?

posts.name: Carter Ryba
posts.cooked: These are the instructions for putting your PDH into recovery mode if you think that will fix it.

link_counts.title: Power Distribution Hub Troubleshooting | REV Robotics Documentation

posts.name: Carter Ryba
posts.cooked: Disconnect the CAN wires from the PDH and see if you have any sticky fault when connected to the PDH then.
